<div id="review_3213889604" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3213889604" />
    <a title="Cindy Rollins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3480406-cindy-rollins"><img alt="Cindy Rollins" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1379169069p2/3480406.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3213889604?book_show_action=true">Mar 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cindy Rollins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cindy Rollins" href="/user/show/3480406-cindy-rollins">Cindy Rollins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20967314-the-blue-castle">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3480406-cindy-rollins?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3213889604" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3102903084732720537">I have to admit that the first half of this book left me wondering why all my friends loved it. Poor Valancy was not really even a sympathetic character only pathetic. Then her bitterness was so profound I found it disturbing and even sadder. The second half of the book is the reason it is so well-loved. <br/>Quite a diversion and quite fun, although I still think her family was a little overdrawn. <br/>Valancy gets her sabbath rest in a cabin in the woods. Let us all embrace our sabbaths with such joy.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


